  "root_text": {
    "dhp21:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp21:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp21:0.3": "Appamādavagga ",
    "dhp21:0.4": "Sāmāvatīvatthu ",
    "dhp21:1": "Appamādo amatapadaṁ, ",
    "dhp21:2": "pamādo maccuno padaṁ; ",
    "dhp21:3": "Appamattā na mīyanti, ",
    "dhp21:4": "ye pamattā yathā matā. ",
    "dhp22:1": "Evaṁ visesato ñatvā, ",
    "dhp22:2": "appamādamhi paṇḍitā; ",
    "dhp22:3": "Appamāde pamodanti, ",
    "dhp22:4": "ariyānaṁ gocare ratā. ",
    "dhp23:1": "Te jhāyino sātatikā, ",
    "dhp23:2": "niccaṁ daḷhaparakkamā; ",
    "dhp23:3": "Phusanti dhīrā nibbānaṁ, ",
    "dhp23:4": "yogakkhemaṁ anuttaraṁ. ",
    "dhp24:0": "Kumbaghosakaseṭṭhivatthu ",
    "dhp24:1": "Uṭṭhānavato satīmato, ",
    "dhp24:2": "Sucikammassa nisammakārino; ",
    "dhp24:3": "Saññatassa dhammajīvino, ",
    "dhp24:4": "Appamattassa yasobhivaḍḍhati. ",
    "dhp25:0": "Cūḷapanthakavatthu ",
    "dhp25:1": "Uṭṭhānenappamādena, ",
    "dhp25:2": "saṁyamena damena ca; ",
    "dhp25:3": "Dīpaṁ kayirātha medhāvī, ",
    "dhp25:4": "yaṁ ogho nābhikīrati. ",
    "dhp26:0": "Bālanakkhattasaṅghuṭṭhavatthu ",
    "dhp26:1": "Pamādamanuyuñjanti, ",
    "dhp26:2": "bālā dummedhino janā; ",
    "dhp26:3": "Appamādañca medhāvī, ",
    "dhp26:4": "dhanaṁ seṭṭhaṁva rakkhati. ",
    "dhp27:1": "Mā pamādamanuyuñjetha, ",
    "dhp27:2": "mā kāmaratisanthavaṁ; ",
    "dhp27:3": "Appamatto hi jhāyanto, ",
    "dhp27:4": "pappoti vipulaṁ sukhaṁ. ",
    "dhp28:0": "Mahākassapattheravatthu ",
    "dhp28:1": "Pamādaṁ appamādena, ",
    "dhp28:2": "yadā nudati paṇḍito; ",
    "dhp28:3": "Paññāpāsādamāruyha, ",
    "dhp28:4": "asoko sokiniṁ pajaṁ; ",
    "dhp28:5": "Pabbataṭṭhova bhūmaṭṭhe, ",
    "dhp28:6": "dhīro bāle avekkhati. ",
    "dhp29:0": "Pamattāpamattadvesahāyakabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp29:1": "Appamatto pamattesu, ",
    "dhp29:2": "suttesu bahujāgaro; ",
    "dhp29:3": "Abalassaṁva sīghasso, ",
    "dhp29:4": "hitvā yāti sumedhaso. ",
    "dhp30:0": "Maghavatthu ",
    "dhp30:1": "Appamādena maghavā, ",
    "dhp30:2": "devānaṁ seṭṭhataṁ gato; ",
    "dhp30:3": "Appamādaṁ pasaṁsanti, ",
    "dhp30:4": "pamādo garahito sadā. ",
    "dhp31:0": "Aññatarabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp31:1": "Appamādarato bhikkhu, ",
    "dhp31:2": "pamāde bhayadassi vā; ",
    "dhp31:3": "Saṁyojanaṁ aṇuṁ thūlaṁ, ",
    "dhp31:4": "ḍahaṁ aggīva gacchati. ",
    "dhp32:0": "Nigamavāsitissattheravatthu ",
    "dhp32:1": "Appamādarato bhikkhu, ",
    "dhp32:2": "pamāde bhayadassi vā; ",
    "dhp32:3": "Abhabbo parihānāya, ",
    "dhp32:4": "nibbānasseva santike. ",
    "dhp32:5": "Appamādavaggo dutiyo. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp21:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp21:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 21–32 ",
    "dhp21:0.3": "2. Diligence ",
    "dhp21:1": "Heedfulness is the state free of death; ",
    "dhp21:2": "heedlessness is the state of death. ",
    "dhp21:3": "The heedful do not die, ",
    "dhp21:4": "while the heedless are like the dead. ",
    "dhp22:1": "Understanding this distinction ",
    "dhp22:2": "when it comes to heedfulness, ",
    "dhp22:3": "the astute rejoice in heedfulness, ",
    "dhp22:4": "happy in the noble ones’ domain. ",
    "dhp23:1": "They who regularly meditate, ",
    "dhp23:2": "always staunchly vigorous; ",
    "dhp23:3": "the attentive realize extinguishment, ",
    "dhp23:4": "the supreme sanctuary from the yoke. ",
    "dhp24:1": "For the hard-working and mindful, ",
    "dhp24:2": "pure of deed and attentive, ",
    "dhp24:3": "restrained, living righteously, and diligent, ",
    "dhp24:4": "their reputation only grows. ",
    "dhp25:1": "By hard work and diligence, ",
    "dhp25:2": "by restraint and by self-control, ",
    "dhp25:3": "a smart person would build an island ",
    "dhp25:4": "that the floods cannot overflow. ",
    "dhp26:1": "Fools and simpletons ",
    "dhp26:2": "devote themselves to negligence. ",
    "dhp26:3": "But the wise protect diligence ",
    "dhp26:4": "as their best treasure. ",
    "dhp27:1": "Don’t devote yourself to negligence, ",
    "dhp27:2": "or delight in erotic intimacy. ",
    "dhp27:3": "For if you’re diligent and meditate, ",
    "dhp27:4": "you’ll attain abundant happiness. ",
    "dhp28:1": "When the astute dispel negligence ",
    "dhp28:2": "by means of diligence, ",
    "dhp28:3": "ascending the palace of wisdom, ",
    "dhp28:4": "sorrowless, they behold this generation of sorrow, ",
    "dhp28:5": "as an attentive one on a mountain top ",
    "dhp28:6": "beholds the fools below. ",
    "dhp29:1": "Heedful among the heedless, ",
    "dhp29:2": "wide awake while others sleep—",
    "dhp29:3": "a true sage leaves them behind, ",
    "dhp29:4": "like a swift horse passing a feeble. ",
    "dhp30:1": "Maghavā became chief of the gods ",
    "dhp30:2": "by means of diligence. ",
    "dhp30:3": "People praise diligence, ",
    "dhp30:4": "while negligence is always deplored. ",
    "dhp31:1": "A mendicant who loves diligence, ",
    "dhp31:2": "seeing fear in negligence—",
    "dhp31:3": "advances like fire, ",
    "dhp31:4": "burning up fetters big and small. ",
    "dhp32:1": "A mendicant who loves diligence, ",
    "dhp32:2": "seeing fear in negligence—",
    "dhp32:3": "such a one can’t decline, ",
    "dhp32:4": "and has drawn near to extinguishment. "
  },
